      <p class="text-body/90 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Components are the building blocks of your Astro application. Learn how to create reusable, performant components with Astro's unique syntax.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-blue-950/30 border-l-4 border-blue-400 p-4 rounded-lg">
        <p class="text-blue-200 text-sm">
          ðŸ’¡ <strong>Key Advantage:</strong> Astro components render to HTML at build time with zero JavaScript by default, resulting in blazing-fast websites.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-6 flex items-center gap-2">
        <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-cyan-400" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"/>
        </svg>
        What are Astro Components?
      </h2>

      <div class="bg-neutral-secondary-soft p-6 rounded-lg border border-default mb-6">
        <p class="text-body/80 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
          Astro components are reusable pieces of UI with a <code class="bg-black/30 px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-cyan-300">.astro</code> extension. They combine:
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-3">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-green-400 font-bold text-xl">âœ“</span>
            <div>
              <strong class="text-white">HTML Template:</strong>
              <span class="text-body/80"> The structure and markup of your component</span>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-green-400 font-bold text-xl">âœ“</span>
            <div>
              <strong class="text-white">Component Script:</strong>
              <span class="text-body/80"> Server-side logic that runs at build time</span>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-green-400 font-bold text-xl">âœ“</span>
            <div>
              <strong class="text-white">Scoped Styles:</strong>
              <span class="text-body/80"> CSS that only applies to this component</span>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-secondary-soft p-6 rounded-lg border border-cyan-500/30">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Basic Component Structure</h3>
        <div class="bg-black/30 p-4 rounded-lg">
          <pre class="text-sm text-cyan-200"><code>{`---
// Component Script (runs on the server)
const greeting = "Hello";
const name = "World";
---

<!-- Component Template (HTML) -->
<div class="greeting">
  <h1>{greeting}, {name}!</h1>
  <p>This is an Astro component.</p>
</div>

<style>
  /* Scoped styles */
  .greeting {
    padding: 1rem;
    background: linear-gradient(to right, cyan, blue);
  }
</style>`}</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-6 flex items-center gap-2">
        <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-cyan-400" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 6v6m0 0v6m0-6h6m-6 0H6"/>
        </svg>
        Creating Your First Component
      </h2>

      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 sm:gap-6 bg-neutral-secondary-soft p-6 rounded-lg border border-default hover:border-cyan-500/50 transition-all duration-300 mb-6 group">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 sm:w-14 sm:h-14 bg-gradient-to-br from-cyan-500 to-blue-500 text-white font-bold text-2xl rounded-full flex items-center justify-center group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform">
          1
        </div>
        <div class="flex-1">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Create a Component File</h3>
          <p class="text-body/80 mb-4">
            Create a new <code class="bg-black/30 px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-cyan-300">.astro</code> file in <code class="bg-black/30 px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-cyan-300">src/components/</code>:
          </p>
          <div class="bg-black/30 p-4 rounded-lg mb-3">
            <p class="text-cyan-300 text-sm mb-2">src/components/Button.astro</p>
            <pre class="text-sm text-cyan-200"><code>{`---
// No props yet - just a simple button
---

<button class="custom-button">
  Click me!
</button>

<style>
  .custom-button {
    padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
    background: #06b6d4;
    color: white;
    border: none;
    border-radius: 0.375rem;
    cursor: pointer;
  }
  
  .custom-button:hover {
    background: #0891b2;
  }
</style>`}</code></pre>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 sm:gap-6 bg-neutral-secondary-soft p-6 rounded-lg border border-default hover:border-cyan-500/50 transition-all duration-300 group">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 sm:w-14 sm:h-14 bg-gradient-to-br from-cyan-500 to-blue-500 text-white font-bold text-2xl rounded-full flex items-center justify-center group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform">
          2
        </div>
        <div class="flex-1">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Use the Component</h3>
          <p class="text-body/80 mb-4">
            Import and use your component in any page or layout:
          </p>
          <div class="bg-black/30 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <p class="text-cyan-300 text-sm mb-2">src/pages/index.astro</p>
            <pre class="text-sm text-cyan-200"><code>{`---
import Button from '../components/Button.astro';
---

<html>
  <body>
    <h1>My Page</h1>
    <Button />
    <Button />
  </body>
</html>`}</code></pre>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-6 flex items-center gap-2">
        <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-cyan-400" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M8 7h12m0 0l-4-4m4 4l-4 4m0 6H4m0 0l4 4m-4-4l4-4"/>
        </svg>
        Component Props
      </h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-neutral-secondary-soft p-6 rounded-lg border border-default">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-cyan-400 mb-3">Defining Props</h3>
          <p class="text-body/80 mb-4">
            Use <code class="bg-black/30 px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-cyan-300">Astro.props</code> to access props passed to your component:
          </p>
          
          <div class="bg-black/30 p-4 rounded-lg mb-4">
            <p class="text-cyan-300 text-sm mb-2">src/components/Greeting.astro</p>
            <pre class="text-sm text-cyan-200"><code>{`---
const { name, age } = Astro.props;
---

<div class="greeting">
  <h2>Hello, {name}!</h2>
  <p>You are {age} years old.</p>
</div>`}</code></pre>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-black/30 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <p class="text-cyan-300 text-sm mb-2">Usage:</p>
            <pre class="text-sm text-cyan-200"><code>{`---
import Greeting from '../components/Greeting.astro';
---

<Greeting name="Alice" age={25} />
<Greeting name="Bob" age={30} />`}</code></pre>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-neutral-secondary-soft p-6 rounded-lg border border-default">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-cyan-400 mb-3">TypeScript Props Interface</h3>
          <p class="text-body/80 mb-4">
            Define a TypeScript interface for type-safe props:
          </p>
          
          <div class="bg-black/30 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <pre class="text-sm text-cyan-200"><code>{`---
interface Props {
  title: string;
  description?: string;
  isPublished?: boolean;
}

const { 
  title, 
  description = "No description provided",
  isPublished = false 
} = Astro.props;
---

<article>
  <h1>{title}</h1>
  <p>{description}</p>
  {isPublished && <span class="badge">Published</span>}
</article>`}</code></pre>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-neutral-secondary-soft p-6 rounded-lg border border-default">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-cyan-400 mb-3">Default Values</h3>
          <p class="text-body/80 mb-4">
            Set default values using destructuring:
          </p>
          
          <div class="bg-black/30 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <pre class="text-sm text-cyan-200"><code>{`---
const { 
  variant = 'primary',
  size = 'medium',
  disabled = false 
} = Astro.props;
---

<button 
  class={\`btn btn-\${variant} btn-\${size}\`}
  disabled={disabled}
>
  <slot />
</button>`}</code></pre>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-6 flex items-center gap-2">
        <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-cyan-400" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M7 21h10a2 2 0 002-2V9.414a1 1 0 00-.293-.707l-5.414-5.414A1 1 0 0012.586 3H7a2 2 0 00-2 2v14a2 2 0 002 2z"/>
        </svg>
        Slots for Content Projection
      </h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-neutral-secondary-soft p-6 rounded-lg border border-default">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-cyan-400 mb-3">Default Slot</h3>
          <p class="text-body/80 mb-4">
            Use <code class="bg-black/30 px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-cyan-300">&lt;slot /&gt;</code> to inject content:
          </p>
          
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            <div class="bg-black/30 p-4 rounded-lg">
              <p class="text-cyan-300 text-sm mb-2">Card.astro</p>
              <pre class="text-xs text-cyan-200"><code>{`---
const { title } = Astro.props;
---

<div class="card">
  <h2>{title}</h2>
  <div class="content">
    <slot />
  </div>
</div>`}</code></pre>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-black/30 p-4 rounded-lg">
              <p class="text-cyan-300 text-sm mb-2">Usage</p>
              <pre class="text-xs text-cyan-200"><code>{`<Card title="My Card">
  <p>This content goes in the slot!</p>
  <button>Click me</button>
</Card>`}</code></pre>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-neutral-secondary-soft p-6 rounded-lg border border-default">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-cyan-400 mb-3">Named Slots</h3>
          <p class="text-body/80 mb-4">
            Create multiple injection points with named slots:
          </p>
          
          <div class="bg-black/30 p-4 rounded-lg mb-3">
            <p class="text-cyan-300 text-sm mb-2">Layout.astro</p>
            <pre class="text-sm text-cyan-200"><code>{`---
---

<div class="layout">
  <header>
    <slot name="header" />
  </header>
  
  <main>
    <slot /> <!-- Default slot -->
  </main>
  
  <aside>
    <slot name="sidebar" />
  </aside>
  
  <footer>
    <slot name="footer" />
  </footer>
</div>`}</code></pre>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-black/30 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <p class="text-cyan-300 text-sm mb-2">Usage with Named Slots</p>
            <pre class="text-sm text-cyan-200"><code>{`<Layout>
  <h1 slot="header">My Website</h1>
  
  <p>This is the main content</p>
  
  <nav slot="sidebar">
    <a href="/">Home</a>
  </nav>
  
  <p slot="footer">Â© 2024</p>
</Layout>`}</code></pre>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-neutral-secondary-soft p-6 rounded-lg border border-default">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-cyan-400 mb-3">Fallback Content</h3>
          <p class="text-body/80 mb-4">
            Provide default content when slot is empty:
          </p>
          
          <div class="bg-black/30 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <pre class="text-sm text-cyan-200"><code>{`---
---

<div class="alert">
  <slot name="icon">
    <!-- Fallback icon if none provided -->
    <svg>...</svg>
  </slot>
  
  <div class="message">
    <slot>
      <!-- Default message -->
      <p>No message provided</p>
    </slot>
  </div>
</div>`}</code></pre>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-6 flex items-center gap-2">
        <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-cyan-400" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M4 5a1 1 0 011-1h4a1 1 0 011 1v7a1 1 0 01-1 1H5a1 1 0 01-1-1V5zM14 5a1 1 0 011-1h4a1 1 0 011 1v7a1 1 0 01-1 1h-4a1 1 0 01-1-1V5zM4 16a1 1 0 011-1h4a1 1 0 011 1v3a1 1 0 01-1 1H5a1 1 0 01-1-1v-3zM14 16a1 1 0 011-1h4a1 1 0 011 1v3a1 1 0 01-1 1h-4a1 1 0 01-1-1v-3z"/>
        </svg>
        Component Composition
      </h2>

      <div class="bg-neutral-secondary-soft p-6 rounded-lg border border-default">
        <p class="text-body/80 mb-4">
          Build complex UIs by composing smaller components:
        </p>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="bg-black/30 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <p class="text-cyan-300 text-sm mb-2">BlogPost.astro</p>
            <pre class="text-sm text-cyan-200"><code>{`---
import Card from './Card.astro';
import Badge from './Badge.astro';
import Author from './Author.astro';

interface Props {
  title: string;
  date: Date;
  tags: string[];
  author: {
    name: string;
    avatar: string;
  };
}

const { title, date, tags, author } = Astro.props;
---

<Card>
  <div slot="header">
    <h2>{title}</h2>
    <time>{date.toLocaleDateString()}</time>
  </div>
  
  <div class="content">
    <slot />
  </div>
  
  <div slot="footer">
    <div class="tags">
      {tags.map(tag => (
        <Badge variant="secondary">{tag}</Badge>
      ))}
    </div>
    <Author {...author} />
  </div>
</Card>`}</code></pre>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-6 flex items-center gap-2">
        <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-cyan-400" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M7 21a4 4 0 01-4-4V5a2 2 0 012-2h4a2 2 0 012 2v12a4 4 0 01-4 4zm0 0h12a2 2 0 002-2v-4a2 2 0 00-2-2h-2.343M11 7.343l1.657-1.657a2 2 0 012.828 0l2.829 2.829a2 2 0 010 2.828l-8.486 8.485M7 17h.01"/>
        </svg>
        Scoped Styles
      </h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-neutral-secondary-soft p-6 rounded-lg border border-default">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">Automatic Scoping</h3>
          <p class="text-body/80 mb-4">
            Styles in <code class="bg-black/30 px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-cyan-300">&lt;style&gt;</code> tags are automatically scoped:
          </p>
          
          <div class="bg-black/30 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <pre class="text-sm text-cyan-200"><code>{`---
const { variant = 'primary' } = Astro.props;
---

<button class={\`btn \${variant}\`}>
  <slot />
</button>

<style>
  .btn {
    padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
    border: none;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    cursor: pointer;
  }
  
  .primary {
    background: #06b6d4;
    color: white;
  }
  
  .secondary {
    background: #64748b;
    color: white;
  }
  
  .btn:hover {
    opacity: 0.9;
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }
</style>`}</code></pre>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-neutral-secondary-soft p-6 rounded-lg border border-default">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">Global Styles</h3>
          <p class="text-body/80 mb-4">
            Use <code class="bg-black/30 px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-cyan-300">:global()</code> for styles that affect children:
          </p>
          
          <div class="bg-black/30 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <pre class="text-sm text-cyan-200"><code>{`<style>
  .container {
    padding: 2rem;
  }
  
  /* This will affect all h1 elements inside .container */
  :global(.container h1) {
    color: #06b6d4;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  
  /* This will affect all links globally */
  :global(a) {
    color: #0891b2;
    text-decoration: none;
  }
</style>`}</code></pre>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-6 flex items-center gap-2">
        <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-cyan-400" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M10 20l4-16m4 4l4 4-4 4M6 16l-4-4 4-4"/>
        </svg>
        Client-Side Scripts
      </h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-neutral-secondary-soft p-6 rounded-lg border border-default">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-cyan-400 mb-3">Adding Interactivity</h3>
          <p class="text-body/80 mb-4">
            Use <code class="bg-black/30 px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-cyan-300">&lt;script&gt;</code> tags for client-side JavaScript:
          </p>
          
          <div class="bg-black/30 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <pre class="text-sm text-cyan-200"><code>{`---
---

<button id="theme-toggle" class="btn">
  Toggle Theme
</button>

<script>
  const button = document.getElementById('theme-toggle');
  
  button?.addEventListener('click', () => {
    document.body.classList.toggle('dark');
    
    const theme = document.body.classList.contains('dark') 
      ? 'dark' 
      : 'light';
    localStorage.setItem('theme', theme);
  });
  
  // Load saved theme
  const savedTheme = localStorage.getItem('theme');
  if (savedTheme === 'dark') {
    document.body.classList.add('dark');
  }
</script>`}</code></pre>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-neutral-secondary-soft p-6 rounded-lg border border-default">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-cyan-400 mb-3">Script Directives</h3>
          <p class="text-body/80 mb-4">
            Control how scripts are processed:
          </p>
          
          <div class="space-y-3">
            <div class="bg-black/30 p-4 rounded-lg">
              <p class="text-cyan-300 text-sm mb-2">Default (bundled & optimized)</p>
              <pre class="text-xs text-cyan-200"><code>{`<script>
  console.log('This gets bundled');
</script>`}</code></pre>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-black/30 p-4 rounded-lg">
              <p class="text-cyan-300 text-sm mb-2">is:inline (not processed)</p>
              <pre class="text-xs text-cyan-200"><code>{`<script is:inline>
  console.log('Runs inline, not bundled');
</script>`}</code></pre>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-black/30 p-4 rounded-lg">
              <p class="text-cyan-300 text-sm mb-2">External script</p>
              <pre class="text-xs text-cyan-200"><code>{`<script src="/scripts/analytics.js"></script>`}</code></pre>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-6 flex items-center gap-2">
        <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-cyan-400" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15 15l-2 5L9 9l11 4-5 2zm0 0l5 5M7.188 2.239l.777 2.897M5.136 7.965l-2.898-.777M13.95 4.05l-2.122 2.122m-5.657 5.656l-2.12 2.122"/>
        </svg>
        Practical Examples
      </h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-neutral-secondary-soft p-6 rounded-lg border border-default">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">Alert Component</h3>
          <div class="bg-black/30 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <pre class="text-sm text-cyan-200"><code>{`---
interface Props {
  type?: 'info' | 'success' | 'warning' | 'error';
  dismissible?: boolean;
}

const { type = 'info', dismissible = false } = Astro.props;
---

<div class={\`alert alert-\${type}\`} role="alert">
  <slot />
  
  {dismissible && (
    <button class="dismiss" aria-label="Dismiss">Ã—</button>
  )}
</div>

{dismissible && (
  <script>
    document.querySelectorAll('.dismiss').forEach(button => {
      button.addEventListener('click', () => {
        button.closest('.alert')?.remove();
      });
    });
  </script>
)}

<style>
  .alert {
    padding: 1rem;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    position: relative;
  }
  
  .alert-info { background: #dbeafe; color: #1e40af; }
  .alert-success { background: #d1fae5; color: #065f46; }
